Title: Use iOS-compatible platform and URL handling

## Problem

KGuiAddons currently treats every Apple platform as macOS:

- It links AppKit and builds the macOS color scheme watcher implementation.
- Its help URL handler attempts to start the desktop `khelpcenter` executable
  with `QProcess`.

AppKit is a macOS framework and is unavailable when targeting iOS. iOS
applications also cannot launch arbitrary external executables, and
`khelpcenter` is not present on the platform. Together these assumptions
prevent KGuiAddons from building for iOS.

## Proposed change

Limit the AppKit-based color scheme watcher to Apple platforms other than iOS.
On iOS, make the KHelpCenter-specific handler report that it did not handle the
URL. This allows the existing caller to fall back to
`QDesktopServices::openUrl()`, which uses the native iOS URL handling path.

## Impact

iOS does not use the macOS AppKit color scheme watcher or KHelpCenter. Help
URLs continue through Qt's platform URL handler. Existing behavior on macOS
and other platforms remains unchanged.

